      </div><p><a name="def_br"></a></p>
<p><strong>Breaking changes</strong></p>
<p>If &ldquo;Breaking?&rdquo; is &ldquo;Yes&rdquo;, the change will break software which relies on the API, and will therefore be introduced in a new API version.</p>
<p>For more details, see the section on <a href="https://developer.service.hmrc.gov.uk/guides/income-tax-mtd-end-to-end-service-guide/documentation/how-to-integrate.html#breaking-changes">breaking changes</a> in the service guide.</p>
<p><a name="def_ty"></a></p>
<p><strong>Tax years</strong></p>
<p>&ldquo;Tax years&rdquo; means the tax years which are affected by the change. &ldquo;YY-YY+&rdquo;&ldquo; indicates that the change affects tax year YY-YY and all later years.</p>
<p><a name="def_aqu"></a></p>
<p><strong>Affects quarterly updates</strong></p>
<p>This means that the change directly impacts MTD mandated customers and their submissions of periodic updates.</p>
<p><a name="def_uiy"></a></p>
<p><strong>Usable in year</strong></p>
<p>This means that the functionality is available during the active tax year to report against. 
For example, transitional profit can be reported during the active tax year.</p>
<p>If &quot;Usable in year?&rdquo; is &ldquo;No&rdquo;, the functionality is not available until after the tax year has ended. 
For example, High Income Child Benefit liability cannot be reported until after the tax year has ended.</p>
<p><a name="def_dep"></a></p>
<p><strong>Deploy to Sandbox</strong></p>
<p>If followed by &ldquo;(pending)&rdquo;, this is the current target date for the change to be available in Sandbox.</p>
<p>If followed by &ldquo;(deployed)&rdquo;, this is the date that the change became available in Sandbox.</p>
